The article discusses the upcoming Fourth of July celebration in the United States. It mentions that Americans have always valued their liberty and paid tribute to those who have sacrificed their lives to defend it. The article also highlights the historical significance of July 4, 1776, when the Declaration of Independence was adopted. It states that President Trump will be delivering remarks at the "Salute to America" event, which will take place on the South Lawn of the White House. The celebration will include the participation of military personnel, first responders, healthcare workers, and others who have played a crucial role in fighting the Coronavirus pandemic. The festivities will feature music, military demonstrations, flyovers, and a fireworks display.